---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { site } from '../lib/site';
---
<Base
  title="Booked — see you soon"
  description="Your AI Opportunity Call is booked. Three things to do before we speak."
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="section ok">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="hud">▸ YOU'RE BOOKED</p>
      <h1 class="ok__title">Booked. I'll see you soon.</h1>
      <p class="lead muted">You're in my calendar, and I'm already looking forward to it. Here's what happens next:</p>

      <ul class="next">
        <li><strong>Right now:</strong> a calendar invite with the video link is on its way to your inbox. If it's not there in five minutes, check spam, then email me directly — <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Before the call:</strong> you'll get a reminder ahead of time. If something comes up, use the reschedule link in the invite. Life happens, just don't ghost me.</li>
        <li><strong>On the call:</strong> 30 minutes, cameras on if you can, and we work. You'll leave with your mini-Map: the top three places AI could genuinely save your team time, in priority order.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="ok__h2">Get the most from your 30 minutes — three things to do before we speak</h2>
      <ol class="prep">
        <li><strong>Jot down the three tasks your team complains about most.</strong> Not what you think the problems are — what they actually moan about. That's usually where the money is.</li>
        <li><strong>Get a rough number for what an hour of team time costs you.</strong> Even a ballpark (salary ÷ hours, plus a bit) turns "annoying" into "£X a week", and that's how we'll prioritise.</li>
        <li><strong>Picture a win in 90 days.</strong> You wrote something in your application — sharpen it. If we did one thing and it worked, what would be different on a Tuesday afternoon?</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="wait reveal">
        <h3>While you wait</h3>
        <p><strong>Read:</strong> <a href="/writing/stop-buying-tools">Stop buying AI tools. Start fixing workflows.</a> Five minutes on why most AI projects stall, and what the ones that don't do differently.</p>
        <p><strong>Then:</strong> <a href="/writing/three-ai-usecases">the three AI use cases most businesses actually need</a>. Useful framing before we talk — bring your reactions along if you like.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ok__actions">
        <a href="/" class="btn">Back home<span class="arrow">→</span></a>
        <a href="/writing" class="btn btn--ghost">Read the writing while you wait</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .ok { padding-block: clamp(3.5rem, 2.5rem + 6vw, 8rem); }
    .container { max-width: 760px; }
    .ok__title { font-size: var(--step-4); margin: 1rem 0 1.2rem; }
    .next { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1.8rem 0 0; display: grid; gap: 0.9rem; max-width: 62ch; }
    .next li { padding-left: 1.7rem; position: relative; }
    .next li::before { content: '✦'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--canary-deep); }
    .next a { color: var(--canary-deep); font-weight: 600; }
    .next a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .ok__h2 { font-size: var(--step-1); margin: 2.6rem 0 0.8rem; }
    .prep { padding-left: 1.3rem; margin: 0.4rem 0 1rem; display: grid; gap: 0.9rem; max-width: 62ch; }
    .prep li::marker { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--canary-deep); font-weight: 700; }
    .wait { background: var(--bone); border: 1px solid var(--line-light); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 1.4rem 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 62ch; }
    .wait h3 { font-size: var(--step-0); font-family: var(--font-display); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
    .wait p { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
    .wait a { color: var(--canary-deep); font-weight: 600; }
    .wait a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .ok__actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 2.4rem; }
  </style>
</Base>
